Privacy Policy
Last updated: March 13, 2025

This Privacy Policy describes our policies and procedures on the collection, use, and disclosure of your information when you use the Service and informs you about your privacy rights and how the law protects you.

We use your personal data to provide and improve the Service. By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

1. Interpretation and Definitions

Interpretation
Words with an initial capital letter have specific meanings as defined below. These definitions apply whether words appear in singular or plural form.

Definitions
For the purposes of this Privacy Policy:

Account: A unique account created for you to access our Service or parts of our Service.
Affiliate: An entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with a party, where "control" means ownership of 50% or more of voting shares or securities.
Application: Refers to Bae Clinic, the software program provided by the Company.
Company: Refers to Bae Clinic, located at Jl. Kayu Tangi 1 Jalur 2 No.99, Sungai Miai, Kec. Banjarmasin Utara, Kota Banjarmasin, Kalimantan Selatan 70123.
Country: Refers to Indonesia.
Device: Any device that can access the Service, such as a computer, cellphone, or digital tablet.
Personal Data: Any information that relates to an identified or identifiable individual.
Service: Refers to the Application.
Service Provider: A third-party company or individual employed by the Company to provide or support the Service.
Third-Party Social Media Service: Any social network website that allows a user to log in or create an account to use the Service.
Usage Data: Data collected automatically when using the Service (e.g., IP address, browser type, session duration).
You: The individual accessing the Service or the company/legal entity on behalf of which the individual is accessing the Service.
2. Collecting and Using Your Personal Data

Types of Data Collected

Personal Data
When using our Service, we may ask you to provide personal information, including but not limited to:

Email address
First name and last name
Phone number
Address, including State, Province, ZIP/Postal code, and City
Usage Data
Usage Data
We collect usage data automatically when using the Service. This may include:

Your device's IP address
Browser type and version
Pages visited on our Service
Time and date of your visit
Time spent on each page
Unique device identifiers
If you access our Service through a mobile device, we may collect additional data, such as:

Mobile device type
Mobile operating system
Unique device identifiers
Mobile browser type and version
Information from Third-Party Social Media Services
You can create an account or log in via the following third-party social media services:

Google
Facebook
Instagram
X (formerly Twitter)
LinkedIn
By using a third-party service to register, you may allow us to access personal data associated with that service (e.g., name, email, contacts).

Information Collected While Using the Application
With your permission, we may collect:

Location data
Camera and photo library access
You can enable or disable access via your device settings at any time.

3. Use of Your Personal Data

The Company may use personal data for the following purposes:

To provide and maintain our Service, including monitoring usage.
To manage your account and provide functionalities available to registered users.
To fulfill contracts, such as processing purchases or service agreements.
To contact you via email, phone, SMS, or push notifications.
To provide marketing and promotional materials, unless you opt out.
To manage your requests, such as customer support.
For business transfers, such as mergers or acquisitions.
For analytical purposes, including service improvement and marketing effectiveness.
Sharing Your Personal Data
Your personal data may be shared in the following cases:

With service providers for operational purposes.
For business transfers, such as mergers or asset sales.
With affiliates, such as parent and subsidiary companies.
With business partners, for joint promotions or offers.
With other users, if you interact in public areas of the Service.
With your consent, for any specific disclosures you approve.
4. Retention and Deletion of Your Personal Data

Retention
We will retain your personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy, or as required by law.

Deletion
You have the right to delete or request deletion of your personal data. You can:

Delete information directly via your account settings.
Contact us to request deletion.
Note that we may retain certain data for legal compliance, fraud prevention, or enforcement of our agreements.
5. Data Security and Transfers

We take reasonable steps to secure your data, but no internet-based service is 100% secure. Your data may be transferred and stored on servers outside your jurisdiction.

If you are in the EU or California, additional data protection rights may apply under GDPR and CCPA.

6. Children's Privacy

Our Service is not intended for children under 13 (or 16 where applicable). If we discover that we have collected data from a minor without parental consent, we will delete it immediately.

7. Legal Compliance

We may disclose your data:

To comply with legal obligations.
To protect our rights or defend against legal claims.
To investigate fraud or security issues.
To protect the safety of users or the public.
8. Third-Party Links

Our Service may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices. Please review their Privacy Policies before using those sites.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page, and we will notify you via:

Email (if applicable)
A notice within the Service
You are encouraged to review this page periodically.

